Cephalothorax:
2.4 long, 1.6 wide. Carapace broadly oval, anteriorly with broad neck, caput raised towards anterior, fovea shallow (
Fig. 31a
); in lateral view highest at midpoint between fovea and eyes (
Fig. 31c
). Labium narrowed anteriorly, about ¾ length of maxillae; chelicerae semi-porrect, with basal transverse ridge, retromargin with single tooth, promargin with three teeth; sternum rounded oval, with precoxal triangles and with smaller, rounded intercoxal extensions (
Fig. 31b
). Posterior eye row slightly recurved, eye group on prominent extension projecting anteriorly over clypeus, eye group occupying 0.6 of carapace width.
